    <name>Angle Tarn and Hayeswater from Patterdale</name>
    <bounds minlat="54.5048998" minlon="-2.9372142" maxlat="54.5384915" maxlon="-2.8782042" />
  </metadata>
  <rte>
    <name>Angle Tarn and Hayeswater from Patterdale</name>
    <desc>This circular Lake District walk from Patterdale features two Lakeland tarns but no summits although with a slight route digression, the Angletarn Pikes could be included as could The Knott. The route offers glorious walking and excellent scenery throughout.</desc>
	<author>Copyright Walking Britain</author>
	<url>www.walkingbritain.co.uk/walk-3670-description</url>
